<p>Dear CoaH Families:</p>



<p>I am writing to provide an update on City on a Hill’s response to the novel Coronavirus (COVID-19). As a reminder, all of our previous messages are archived <a href="https://www.cityonahill.org/covid-19/">here</a>.</p>



<p>Earlier today, <a href="https://www.bostonglobe.com/2020/04/21/nation/coronavirus-boston-massachusetts-april-21/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Governor Charlie Baker extended the closure of all Massachusetts schools through the remainder of the current school year.  (opens in a new tab)">Governor Charlie Baker extended the closure of all Massachusetts schools through the remainder of the current school year. </a>City on a Hill Boston and City on a Hill New Bedford will be closed during this period as well. <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/18/us/schools-closed-coronavirus/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Massachusetts joins more than 30 other states in making the same choice. (opens in a new tab)">Massachusetts joins more than 30 other states in making the same choice.</a><br></p>



